Docker file is a blue print who define the way to build docker image and container.
  docker file will have some instruction which is the direction of dockerizing application.



FROM: It pull the base image from the docker hub.
  FROM BASE_IMAGE. 

WORKDIR: all command that is run in the docker file will be stored in the workdir.

COPY: This is used for copying file or folder from host machine to image

RUN: This will run all instruction one by one inside the docker image

CMD: This will run the docker file.

EXPOSE: We will expose our port by using EXPOSE.

ENV: We declare the required environment using ENV
  
